UI Controls for Freestyle Pages

Drag controls from the Controls tab to the Canvas on the UI Editor in the Prototype tool to a them to a freestyle prototype page.

Table 2. UI Controls for Freestyle Prototype Pages

Control

Image

Description

More information
Buttonpane

A button is used for navigation, can also be used to perform various actions such as show alert, trigger a dialog, and so on. You can customize the behaviour of a button in the Actions section of the Properties panel. https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/button/
Link

A Link is text that users can click to navigate to a specified URL or web page, you can enter the desired display text and specify the destination URL in the Properties panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/link/

Hotspot

Hotspot is typically used to enable actions on an image or any static element. Drag and drop the Hotspot control over an image, resize it and specify what action occurs on clicking the hotspot in the Actions section of the Properties panel.

Link Image Pages in Page Map View
Tile

A Tile is typically used for launching apps and presenting them on a launchpad. A tile displays information users select to perform an action. In Properties, you can customize the icon, define the title, and choose additional information to display. In Actions, you can define what happens when a user selects the tile.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/concept/tile/

Toggle Button

A button that can be toggled between selected and unselected state.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/button/

Icon Tab Bar

The icon tab bar comprises a series of tabs that each link to a different content area or views. Users can switch between views by clicking or tapping the respective tab. You can add more views by dragging and dropping Icon Tabs. Each view can be customized by dragging and dropping controls in it.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/icontabbar/

Icon Tab

An Icon Tab is used to add another content area or view to an icon tab bar. Once added, the content area can be customized by dragging and dropping desired controls in it. https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/icontabbar/
Tab Separator

A Tab Separator visually enhances Icon Tab Bar by separating the tab buttons. Position it between two Icon Tabs.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/icontabbar/

Item Header

An Item Header contains the most important information a user needs to see about an item, such as its image, name, and status. You can add more Item Attributes or Item Statusesby dragging and dropping them into the Item Header control.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/object-list-item/

Item Status

An Item Status displays various statuses for an item - neutral, positive, negative, and critical. For example, you may use it if you want to show the status of a package - whether it has been shipped, delayed, or cancelled. You can drag it directly onto the canvas or into another control.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/object-display-elements/

Item Identifier

Short text that represents the key identifier of an item. Drag it onto the canvas or another control, position it, and then in Properties define the Label and Text.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/object-display-elements/

Item Number

Short text that represents the numeric attribute of an item and its unit. Drag it onto the canvas or another control, position it, and then in Properties define the Number, Item, and State.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/object-display-elements/

Item Attribute

An Item Attribute displays information about an item. Unlike the Label, Text, and Item Status controls, you can define what happens when users interact with the Item Attribute control in the Actions section of the Properties panel.

http://sap.github.io/BUILD_User_Assistance/BUILD/89e8760b9158475aa4cfd9ed15c69297.html

Image

The Image control allows you to integrate images into your apps. You can upload your images by clicking Library in the Properties panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/image/

Label

The Label control is used for the name or title of a control or group of related controls. It is usually used in forms for clarification purposes. If you want to place some text but you are not labeling something, or if you would like to have multiple lines of text, use the Text control instead.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/label/

Text

Text control can accommodate multiple lines of text.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/text/

Title

Item Attribute controls, you can define the font size of your title in the Properties panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/title/

Icon

Build with embedded font, icons scale well and can trigger and event if selected. In Properties, select LIBRARY to select an icon, define the size, and in Actions define what happens if it’s selected.

http://sap.github.io/BUILD_User_Assistance/Splash/2269877a7c2348d59d4a5deaa0e4d90a.html#loio2269877a7c2348d59d4a5deaa0e4d90a

Progress Indicator

Visualizes the current advancement of a process or a degree of accomplishment. The inside of the progress indicator is filled with color to indicate the state of progress. The advancement depends on the specific process. The progress is shown either using absolute numbers or the current percentage of completion together with a progress bar.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/progress-indicator/

Toolbar Spacer

 Assists you in aligning controls neatly. Resize it using the green handles, and position other controls in relation to it. It isn’t displayed in prototypes. http://sap.github.io/BUILD_User_Assistance/Splash/4034a659577d4d5fa725af4c3525eb2d.html

Image Carousel

Enables users to browse through a set of items. It always displays one item at a time. From the displayed item, the user can navigate to either the next or the previous item. The interaction resembles browsing through the pages of a book.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/carousel/

Simple Form

Presents data to the user and enables them to enter data in a structured way. Add more controls from the ADD combo-boxes in the Content section on the CHILDREN tab on the right panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/form/

Advanced Form

Presents data to the user and enables them to enter data in a structured way. You can define the layout in the Form Layout control, which is added automatically. Add more controls from the ADD combo-boxes in the sections on the CHILDREN tab on the right panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/form/

Form Container

You can drag multiple Form Container controls to Advanced Forms. Each contain Form Elements. You can drag and drop more Form Element controls onto it.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/form/

Form Element

You can drag multiple Form Element controls onto Form Containers in Advanced Forms. Each contains a Label and Field controls, and add more controls from the ADD combo-boxes in the CHILDREN tab on the right panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/form/

Grid

Position UI controls in a 12-column flow layout. You can set a Grid to display a variable number of columns depending on screen size. Add more controls from the ADD combo-boxes in the CHILDREN tab.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/foundation/grid-layout/

Horizontal Box

Displays a selection of controls horizontally in a structured way. Define the alignment, height, and direction of the box. Add more controls from the ADD combo-boxes in the CHILDREN tab on the right panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/responsive-table/

Vertical Box

Displays a selection of controls vertically in a structured way. Define the alignment, height, and direction of the box. Add more controls from the ADD combo-boxes in the CHILDREN tab on the right panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/responsive-table/

Nested Box

Displays a selection of controls in a structured way. Define the alignment, height, and direction of the box. Add more controls from the ADD combo-boxes in the CHILDREN tab on the right panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/responsive-table/

Panel

Displays a container for grouping and displaying information. It can be collapsed to save space on the screen. Use to enable use to display additional information on demand.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/panel/

Table

Contains a set of line items, and is responsive to the display format. Similar to List controls, but data in a Table is more complex. Depending on the scenario, users can navigate from the line items to further details. Right-click on the table to display a contextual menu that enables you to do the following:

  • Copy the selected column or row
  • Paste a previously selected column or row
  • Delete the selected column or row
  • Add a column or row before the selected column or row
  • Add a column or row after the selected column or row
  • Clear the content of the select column or row

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/responsive-table/

Column

Displays the vertical values on a Table control. Add a header and footer to a column from the ADD combo-boxes in the CHILDREN tab on the right panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/responsive-table/

Row

 Displays the vertical values on a Table control. Add controls to empty cells by selecting a row, and then selecting a control from the ADD combo-box on the CHILDREN tab on the right panel. https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/responsive-table/

Feed list

Feed list item

List

The list is a responsive container that displays multiple List Item controls. Similar to Table controls, but data in a List is more basic. Add or delete List Items and Standard List Items.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/list-overview/

List Item

Contained in a List, a List Item contains important information about the item, including an Intro, a Title, and Icon, a Number with unit and status. You can add more Item Attributes and Item Statuses.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/object-list-item/

Standard List Item

Use for less complex entries in a List, like a user selecting an item in a dialog, it contains information including an Icon, a Title, a Description, Info, and Info Status.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/standard-list-item/

Object Header

Displays controls in structured way. It is added to an Object Page Sub-Section. You can add more Attributes and Statuses from the CHILDREN tab on the right panel.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/object-header/

Object Page Section

Users can easily navigate to the content of an Object Page Section by selecting the name of the section beneath the Object Page Header. You can add more Object Page Sections, and add more Object Page Sub-Sections to each.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/floorplans/object-page/

Calendar

Enables users to view a one or more calendar months simultaneously. Optionally, enable users to select one or a sequence of dates, and also define how many months to display.

Calendar Date Interval

Enables users to view a range of dates in a single row. Optionally, enable users to select one or a sequence of dates, and also define how many days to display simultaneously.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/calendar-date-interval/

Date Picker

Enables users to select a localized date. It consists of two parts: the date input field and the date picker. Use this control if the user needs to enter a single date or a date range.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/date-picker/

Date Time Input

Enables users to select and display a date, a time, or both. You can define what occurs if the user selects a time or date.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/date-time-input/

Check Box

Enables users to set a binary value, such as true or false. Selecting it toggles between checked and unchecked. Checked means that the state or item described by the checkbox text applies.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/checkbox/

Combo Box

Enables users to select from a drop-down list of item. The user can filter the drop-down list by entering text. Add more items by dragging Combo Box Items controls onto the Combo Box.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/combo-box/

Combo Box item

An item on a Combo Box drop-down list. Drag it on a Combo Box control, and in Properties enter the name of the item in Text.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/combo-box/

Radio Button

Enables users to select only one option from two or more choices. Add two or more Radio Button controls to enable users to select one of a number of options.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/radio-button/
Input

Enables users to enter and edit text or numeric values in one line. In Properties, define the type and format of the information users can enter, such as Date, Email, Password, Url, and Text.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/input-field/

Rating Indicator

Enables users to rate an item on a numeric scale. The most popular scale is 1 to 5, where a rating of 1 is worse than a rating of 5. Often added to List Items.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/rating-indicator/

Switch

Enables users to toggle between two options, such as ON and OFF. You can define the toggle text, and define actions that occur if the user toggles the switch.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/switch/

Text Area

Enables users to enter multiple lines of text. You can define the number of rows and placeholder text, and define actions that occur if users enter text.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/text-area/

Chart

Users view data represented as horizontal bars. Measures, which contain numerical data, like Profit, are on the horizontal axis, and dimensions, containing categorical data, are on the vertical axis. It can have one dimension and up to three measures. You can add data using the Data Editor and bind it to a Chart.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart/

Bar Chart

Users view data represented as horizontal bars. Measures, which contain numerical data, like Profit, are on the horizontal axis, and dimensions, containing categorical data, are on the vertical axis. It can have one dimension and up to three measures. You can add data using the Data Editor and bind it to a Bar Chart.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-toolbar/

Line Chart

Users view data represented as a series of data points connected by straight lines. Measures, which contain numerical data, like Profit, are on the horizontal axis, and dimensions, containing categorical data, like Country, are on the vertical axis. It can have one dimension and up to three measures. You can add data using the Data Editor and bind it to a Line Chart.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-toolbar/

Column Chart

Users view data represented as vertical bars. Measures, which contain numerical data, like Profit, are on the vertical axis, and dimensions, containing categorical data, like Country, are on the horizontal axis. It can have one dimension and up to three measures. You can add data using the Data Editor and bind it to a Column Chart.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-toolbar/

Pie Chart

Users view data represented as circle divided into portions. Measures, which contain numerical data, like Profit, are reflect in the sizes of the portions, and dimensions, containing categorical data, like Country, are reflected in the color-coded legend. A Pie Chart can have one dimension and up to one measure. You can add data using the Data Editor and bind it to a Pie Chart.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-toolbar/

Horizontal Bullet Chart

Compare a primary value to a secondary value, called the comparison value, which is represented as a line across a value bar. Similar to a Bar Chart, but with enriched mean for qualitative ranges of performance, such as poor, satisfactory, and good.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-types/bullet-chart/

Vertical Bullet Chart

 Compare a primary value to a secondary value, called the comparison value, which is represented as a line across a value bar. Similar to a Bar Chart, but with enriched mean for qualitative ranges of performance, such as poor, satisfactory, and good.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-types/bullet-chart/

Stacked Bar Chart

Users view complex comparisons between groups of data, represented as horizontal bars. Each bar is divided into color-coded areas, with each color representing a group. A value is displayed for each group within each bar. Groups are in the same sequence in each bar. The length of the bar shows the combined result of the groups. Do not use if some groups have negative values. Use to display complex comparisons.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-types/

Stacked Column Chart

Users view comparisons between groups of data, represented as vertical bars. Each bar is divided into color-coded areas, with each color representing a group. A value is displayed for each group within each bar. Groups are in the same sequence in each bar. The height of the bar shows the combined result of the groups. Do not use if some groups have negative values. Use to display complex comparisons between groups

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-types/

Scatter Chart

Users view data represented as a collection of points. The position of each point is determined by two variables, one determining the position on the horizontal axis and the other determining the position on the vertical axis. For example, the horizontal axis can be date and time, and the vertical axis can be sales. Use if you want to show nonlinear relationships between values.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-types/

Bubble Chart

Users view data represented as bubbles. Each bubble represents three dimensions of data: a variable on the horizontal axis, a variable on the vertical access, and a variable for the size of the bubble. Users view data, either numbers or text, displayed within the bubbles. Use to represent social, economic, or other scientific relationships.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-types/

Waterfall Chart

Users view data represented as vertical bars. Bars do not necessarily start on the horizontal axis. Each bar represents a range of variables on the vertical axis, corresponding to a variable on the horizontal axis. Use to demonstrate how a cumulative value changes from an initial state to a final state by representing the accumulation of successive values.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-types/

Heatmap Chart

Users view data in two dimensions where values are represented just by color. If you have a lot of categories, the heat map might not render correctly on small devices. Use if the categories you’re comparing contain many items, and you’re just interested in showing approximate values.

https://experience.sap.com/fiori-design-web/ui-components/chart-types/
